value.0: Hollis Redwheel II, called "Holly" by the townsfolk to distinguish him from his grandfather, is a timid young boy. Preferring the company of the cart oxen to most people, he is a remarkably well-behaved child with an imagination that seems to keep him intensely occupied. Though only 8, he has a way with green growing things that astonishes many of the adults- his family's plot, thanks to Holly, gives the town most of its fresh produce.

Over three decades ago, a handcraftsman by the name of Jasper went to gather flotsam from the shoreline. Jasper crafted furniture, knick-knacks, and other souvenirs from the material. One day he returned carrying a young elfin boy in his arms, skin dark like the bark of the black cherry tree. Jasper never spoke of how he came into possession of the child, but he raised the child as his own and named him Karyon. When Karyon came of age and showed an aptitude for magic, Jasper bid him to go and learn of his people in Winya Ravena. Years later, when Jasper was upon his deathbed, Karyon returned from Winya and, in a decision that surprised many in the village, chose to stay and carry on something of Jasper's trade in the predominantly human fishing village.
A black robe.  Fine for walking about town, and being seen at the Nomad.  Not very practical for battle however.
A member of the Moonpier Militia. He seems intent on his duties of protecting the town. His equipment appears to be of high grade and bears a small makers mark fashioned to look like a rainbow trout.

Jonah is a town joy in Moonpier. Sweet, kind, gentle and not good at sailing whatsoever, he provides the much needed job of securing boats and ships to the dock when they arrive. He's been there his whole life and doesn't seem to ever leave the docks, preferring the company of the fish and water to his fellows. He speaks in short phrases and don't be heard calling him simple-minded anywhere in the town -- he's their little Jonah, so you better back off.

Granddaughter of Hollis Redwheel, Valridian is known as "The Maiden" to the townsfolk, though sailors are extremely careful never to let her hear the nickname. She spends most of her day by the docks, gutting and filleting the day's catch for sale, a job she started at the tender age of 8.

As a woman who has spent her entire life in the company of hard-worn sailors, as a matter of survival, she curses harder, holds her liquor better, and can throw a meaner right hook than any man in the town. She has two children, born out of wedlock and rumored to be the offspring of Sergeant Doran.
Daughter of Valridian Redwheel and older sister to Holly, Almarie is a town treasure. With a dimpled smile and kind brown eyes, she spends most of her time playing by the docks.

Always quick with a joke and a smile, Doran is the life of every party in the village. With a booming voice, round red cheeks, and dark hair, he's universally liked in Moonpier (except by the various women by which he has children and thus far has refused to marry). He still has the Southport accent of his father, but moved early in life to Moonpier and adjusted to living there quite well.

Now a leader of the Moonpier Militia. He seems intent on his duties of protecting the town. His equipment appears to be of high grade and bears a small maker's mark fashioned to look like a rainbow trout.

Light weaponry is oft looked down upon by the masses as the tools of cowards and weaklings. A dagger cannot put fear in an opponent like a glistening long sword. At least, not until a group of thieves, assassins and other nightwalkers known as the Guild of the Red Moon started carrying light weaponry that could punch through plate smooth as silk and quietly as a whisper. The Sureforged, as they are now known, are a must have commodity for any respectable adventurer who prefers his slaughter silent.

Refined and pressed into a liquid, this belladonna extract is extremely potent compared to the raw herb.

You can easy use this in small doses and still have a more effective means than chewing a leave.

A gnomish fellow. He looks excited about something.

Value.value: Hello, hello! Hi! It's a pleasure! I have something I need someone like you to do for me!
Have you heard of the Electric Castle? No? Well, even if you had, I'll tell you all about it! Or I would if I knew everything I wanted to know about it.

I need you to go into Malarfang Forest and bring me back something unique and exciting! Preferably something that belongs to that lich that's in there. So many liches around! What? Yes, it's perfectly safe.
Well, that's a little unexpected. But it works! Thanks! Here, have your gold.
Oh, you'll find the Malarfang Forest through this here gate! Just follow the road till it turns and plunges into the forest! You'll miss it if you go too far, though. I'm sure you'll find it.

Hello, hello again, adventurer! Yes. Are you looking for more errands? Well, I don't have anything, but I hear there's something to do up north in Fort Cystana! They like to  send do-gooders on adventures.
I'll pay you in gold if you fetch me something of his! Yes, plenty of gold, but also the joy of exploring something so... so... prestigious! I hear there's a maze and everything!

value.0: Reggie is an excited little wizard who looks like he has something to say.

Value.value: G-Greetings! I'm l-looking for someone to g-go south along the c-coast here!
I-I've been told that there's a nasty s-s-s... lich holed up in an underground tomb.
I-I would go myself, but y-y-you see I don't have a research team to protect m-me.
Th-This could work! Thank y-you so much! Here, have your coin!
Th-The crypt should be d-due south from here. I-I'm sure it's off the road s-somewhere along the way. J-Just keep looking. I'm s-sure you'll find it!
S-Splendid to s-see you! Have you checked in with my colleage? H-He's up north by the o-other gate and m-might have errands a-also!
I-If you find it and bring me something th-that belonged to the lich, I c-could maybe see about finding some w-way to get rid of its ph-phylactery!
And I-I-I'll pay you! I'll pay you in gold!
